#compdef wally
# =============================================================================
# wally — Uplift Games' "Wally is a modern package manager for
#         Roblox projects inspired by Cargo" — a Rust-implemented
#         package manager for Roblox Luau projects, modeling its
#         CLI surface + manifest format directly on Cargo (the
#         Rust package manager).  Distinguishing from rotriever
#         (Roblox's official package tool), foreman (toolchain
#         manager), aftman (toolchain manager), and other Roblox
#         tooling by:
#           - CARGO-PARALLEL CLI: `wally init` / `wally install`
#             / `wally update` / `wally publish` / `wally login`
#             / `wally search` — every command mirrors the
#             equivalent `cargo` command for Rust developers
#             transitioning to Roblox Luau development
#           - wally.toml MANIFEST FORMAT: TOML-based manifest
#             with [package] / [dependencies] / [dev-dependencies]
#             / [server-dependencies] sections paralleling
#             Cargo.toml
#           - SEMVER DEPENDENCY RESOLUTION: full semver range
#             support ("^0.5.0", ">=1.0.0, <2.0.0")
#             matching Cargo's npm-style resolution
#           - GIT-BACKED PACKAGE REGISTRY: wally packages are
#             published to a Git-backed registry (default
#             https://github.com/UpliftGames/wally-index);
#             custom registries supported
#           - SCOPED PACKAGES: package names have @scope/name
#             format (e.g. @roblox/roact); analogous to npm
#             scopes
#           - REALM-SEPARATED DEPENDENCIES: server/shared/dev
#             realm separation — packages can be installed into
#             ServerScriptService vs ReplicatedStorage vs DevOnly
#             based on which dependency section they're in
#           - PACKAGE SUBCOMMAND with download/extract sub-
#             subcommands for low-level registry interaction
#           - manifest-to-json: convert wally.toml to JSON for
#             tooling integration
#           - figment-LAYERED CONFIGURATION: registry endpoint +
#             auth tokens + cache paths loaded via figment's
#             Provider trait abstraction (TOML config files +
#             environment variables + CLI overrides)
#         Used by: Roblox game developers using Luau (Roblox's
#         strongly-typed Lua dialect), Studio plugin authors
#         shipping community libraries, and as a reference
#         implementation of Cargo-style package management for
#         non-Rust ecosystems.
#
# Author:  Uplift Games (uplift-games organization on GitHub) —
#          Roblox game studio.  Started as Lucien Greathouse's
#          (LPGhatguy) personal project + adopted by Uplift
#          Games for the open-source Roblox community.  License:
#          MPL-2.0.
# Source:  https://github.com/UpliftGames/wally
#          https://github.com/UpliftGames/wally/blob/master/src/main.rs
#          https://github.com/UpliftGames/wally/blob/master/src/commands/mod.rs
# CLI:     src/main.rs + src/commands/mod.rs — uses structopt
#          (clap derive's predecessor, now superseded by
#          clap derive in modern Rust but still actively used).
#          Headline library: **figment** (structopt is widely
#          documented across many Rust completions; figment is
#          the new variant being documented here, expanding
#          Axis 13 to 2 Rust variants).
# Library: figment (https://github.com/SergioBenitez/Figment)
#          ("figment" — Sergio Benitez (SergioBenitez on GitHub,
#           also author of Rocket web framework) — released 2020
#           as "A hierarchical configuration library so con-free,
#           it's unreal".  Distinct from config-rs (R629, the
#           Rust Axis 13 opener) by being:
#             1. PROVIDER TRAIT ABSTRACTION — figment's central
#                feature is the `Provider` trait, which any
#                configuration source implements.  Each Provider
#                produces a `Profile` map that figment merges:
#                  use figment::{Figment, providers::{Env, Toml, Json}};
#                  let config = Figment::new()
#                      .merge(Toml::file("App.toml"))
#                      .merge(Json::file("App.json"))
#                      .merge(Env::prefixed("APP_"));
#             2. BUILT-IN PROVIDERS — figment ships 7+ providers
#                via features:
#                  * Toml::file(path) / Toml::string(s)
#                  * Json::file(path) / Json::string(s)
#                  * Yaml::file(path) / Yaml::string(s)
#                  * Env::prefixed("APP_") / Env::raw()
#                  * Serialized::defaults(struct_instance)
#                  * Format trait for custom formats
#             3. PROFILE-AWARE CONFIGURATION — every value belongs
#                to a Profile (default / debug / release / custom
#                names).  Profile selection happens at extraction
#                time via `Figment::select(profile)`, matching
#                Rocket's "Rocket.toml has [global], [debug],
#                [release] sections" pattern
#             4. ROCKET-FRAMEWORK PROVENANCE — figment is Rocket
#                web framework's configuration library, extracted
#                as a standalone crate.  Used by EVERY Rocket
#                application transitively for app config loading
#             5. ROUTING ERROR MESSAGES — when extraction fails,
#                figment reports the SOURCE provider, the OFFENDING
#                key path, and the EXPECTED type — better debugging
#                than config-rs's flat errors
#             6. SERIALIZED PROVIDER — Figment can take a struct
#                instance with serde::Serialize as the base
#                configuration, allowing programmatic config
#                construction without serializing to TOML/YAML
#                first
#             7. SERGIO-BENITEZ ECOSYSTEM PROVENANCE — Sergio is
#                also the author of Rocket (5-year-leading Rust
#                web framework), Sailfish (templating), and Rocket's
#                full ecosystem; figment is "production
#                infrastructure" extracted for general use)
# License: MPL-2.0 (wally); MIT OR Apache-2.0 (figment)
# Status:  wally — 477+ stars on UpliftGames/wally, widely
#          adopted in the Roblox developer community; figment —
#          898+ stars on SergioBenitez/Figment, ~50M crates.io
#          downloads, foundational dependency of Rocket (24k+
#          stars web framework) + slatedb/slatedb (3k stars) +
#          cnosdb/cnosdb (1.7k stars) + LukeMathWalker/pavex
#          (2k stars) + UpliftGames/wally (THIS — 477 stars) +
#          metaplex-foundation projects + Cubist multichain SDK
#          + Dstack-TEE/dstack (confidential AI framework) +
#          900+ Rust applications using Provider-trait
#          configuration.
#
